· Verification, “Are you building it right?” seeks an answer to the question.
So “Are you building it right?”.
Validation is “Are you building the right thing?” seeks an answer to the question.
So “Are you building the right thing?”.
· Verification is done by software developers (developer), while Validation is done by test engineers.
· Verification is an objective process and no subjective judgment is required to validate the software.
 Validation, on the other hand, is a subjective process and includes subjective decisions about how well a
 software works.